00:19:49,493 --> 00:19:51,513
[music]

274
00:19:57,840 --> 00:20:00,319
He definitely ended up with Monika.

275
00:20:00,320 --> 00:20:03,799
He’s not even making a sound.

276
00:20:07,520 --> 00:20:10,079
And he's a bit absent-minded too.

277
00:20:10,080 --> 00:20:12,879
I wonder where his head is at. Is he thinking

278
00:20:12,880 --> 00:20:15,880
about her?

279
00:20:24,864 --> 00:20:26,884
[music]

280
00:20:27,440 --> 00:20:29,519
What’s wrong? Is something bothering you? You keep

281
00:20:29,520 --> 00:20:31,759
sighing.

282
00:20:31,760 --> 00:20:33,918
The weather’s weird.

283
00:20:33,919 --> 00:20:37,079
It’s gotten totally unstable, that’s why.

284
00:20:37,080 --> 00:20:40,639
Just like people. They’re unstable too.

285
00:20:40,640 --> 00:20:42,959
One day sunny, one day rainy.

286
00:20:42,960 --> 00:20:44,999
If you trust it and head out, you’re guaranteed

287
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:47,239
to get soaked. I mean, I don’t get how they

288
00:20:47,240 --> 00:20:49,439
can change so fast.

289
00:20:49,440 --> 00:20:52,199
Those people who say one thing and do another

290
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:55,558
really get on my nerves,

291
00:20:55,559 --> 00:20:58,158
right? You shouldn’t make promises and then do

292
00:20:58,159 --> 00:20:59,359
something else.

293
00:20:59,360 --> 00:21:02,918
I agree, people should be clear and straightforward.

294
00:21:02,919 --> 00:21:06,399
Where are they? Always playing games and

295
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:09,279
not even knowing what they want.

296
00:21:09,280 --> 00:21:11,319
Everyone’s gotten weird.

297
00:21:11,320 --> 00:21:13,719
You really can’t trust anyone.

298
00:21:13,720 --> 00:21:17,360
Picking the right companion matters.

299
00:21:20,480 --> 00:21:24,360
Could you hand me that file?

300
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:28,398
Sorry for the trouble.

301
00:21:28,399 --> 00:21:30,419
[music]

302
00:21:34,440 --> 00:21:36,999
Do you have some problem with me?

303
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:40,880
What problem could I have with you?

304
00:21:42,159 --> 00:21:43,639
Okay. I get that you’re bothered by me,

305
00:21:43,640 --> 00:21:45,959
but we’re working here. You keep talking

306
00:21:45,960 --> 00:21:48,239
to me all snappy and stuff.

307
00:21:48,240 --> 00:21:49,200
That’s not okay.

308
00:21:49,201 --> 00:21:51,239
You’re the one talking to me like that.

309
00:21:51,240 --> 00:21:53,798
I’m just reacting. And you keep giving me

310
00:21:53,799 --> 00:21:56,558
those hard stares.

311
00:21:56,559 --> 00:21:59,559
Oh God.

312
00:22:02,559 --> 00:22:07,480
See, you’re always looking at me like that.

313
00:22:10,360 --> 00:22:13,319
And you’re always yelling

314
00:22:13,320 --> 00:22:16,120
and shouting at me.

315
00:22:18,360 --> 00:22:21,360
Don’t look at me,

316
00:22:22,799 --> 00:22:26,038
look at Monica or something.

317
00:22:26,039 --> 00:22:28,839
What did you say? Did you say something?

318
00:22:28,840 --> 00:22:31,239
I said that would be good.

319
00:22:31,240 --> 00:22:36,440
Don’t look at me. Go look at whoever you want.

320
00:22:45,600 --> 00:22:49,158
I don’t want to bother you.

321
00:22:49,159 --> 00:22:52,240
That’s for the best.

322
00:22:52,895 --> 00:22:53,880
[music]

323
00:22:53,881 --> 00:22:56,519
I’m asking you one last time. This time

324
00:22:56,520 --> 00:22:59,444
be honest.

325
00:22:59,445 --> 00:23:04,000
[music] What’s wrong? Tell me.

326
00:23:05,120 --> 00:23:06,798
I'm fine, nothing's wrong.

327
00:23:06,799 --> 00:23:09,924
Just leave me alone already.

328
00:23:09,925 --> 00:23:11,945
[music]

329
00:23:24,799 --> 00:23:27,839
If Haydır knows about this, we're in big trouble,

330
00:23:27,840 --> 00:23:32,799
and if he doesn't, we're in even bigger trouble.

331
00:23:36,039 --> 00:23:37,918
Stop running around like a headless chicken

332
00:23:37,919 --> 00:23:39,999
and listen to me.

333
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:42,678
Either you hand the presidency over to me or

334
00:23:42,679 --> 00:23:44,640
I'll tell everyone that you're a lowly thief,

335
00:23:44,641 --> 00:23:47,319
with music and all.

336
00:23:47,320 --> 00:23:49,839
I really can't deal with you right now. My head's

337
00:23:49,840 --> 00:23:53,119
full of a thousand different things. Get out of my face.

338
00:23:53,120 --> 00:23:56,199
I guess you didn't understand. Either you hand

339
00:23:56,200 --> 00:23:59,319
over the presidency to me or everyone will find out

340
00:23:59,320 --> 00:24:01,999
you're a thief.

341
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:04,879
In that case you'll be thrown out of the presidency anyway.

342
00:24:04,880 --> 00:24:08,639
I'm giving you an option.

343
00:24:08,640 --> 00:24:13,039
All I can do for you is curse you.

344
00:24:13,200 --> 00:24:16,678
Here, take the presidency, it's yours.

345
00:24:16,679 --> 00:24:20,679
Just leave me in peace.

346
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:26,319
Leave the Yıldırıms in peace. Hah, you haven't

347
00:24:26,320 --> 00:24:29,880
seen anything yet, have you?

348
00:24:33,640 --> 00:24:35,719
Oh God,

349
00:24:35,720 --> 00:24:39,080
how could I forget?

350
00:24:41,960 --> 00:24:43,719
Hello

351
00:24:43,720 --> 00:24:47,239
You're absolutely right, my girl. I forgot. Oh God.

352
00:24:47,240 --> 00:24:49,798
How could I forget? Of course I'd come,

353
00:24:49,799 --> 00:24:52,678
my beautiful girl. I'm coming right away.

354
00:24:52,679 --> 00:24:55,679
Okay.

355
00:24:55,919 --> 00:24:58,919
Mom

356
00:24:59,159 --> 00:25:02,479
where are you going?

357
00:25:02,480 --> 00:25:06,038
Well, I have something to do, my girl.

358
00:25:06,039 --> 00:25:07,639
What do you have to do?

359
00:25:07,640 --> 00:25:10,079
Do I have to report to you? I have some Aslı business,

360
00:25:10,080 --> 00:25:14,480
that's all. I'm going out, I'm going for a walk.

361
00:25:25,720 --> 00:25:30,559
Monika, I'm ready. Let's go out.

362
00:25:40,559 --> 00:25:43,798
I broke the frame.

363
00:25:43,799 --> 00:25:45,519
And she had the frame fixed and put it

364
00:25:45,520 --> 00:25:48,520
in the drawer.

365
00:25:52,799 --> 00:25:55,519
What does that mean now, Cemal?

366
00:25:55,520 --> 00:25:58,558
I mean, women are a bit, I don't know,

367
00:25:58,559 --> 00:26:00,398
complicated.

368
00:26:00,399 --> 00:26:02,359
Even if you spread the world at their feet,

369
00:26:02,360 --> 00:26:04,719
they say it doesn't work here. They wish you'd laid it over there.

370
00:26:04,720 --> 00:26:06,719
So I think you should look at the result. I mean,

371
00:26:06,720 --> 00:26:08,079
the fact that she even had the frame fixed [music]

372
00:26:08,080 --> 00:26:12,200
means she's still leaving a door open for you.

373
00:26:21,159 --> 00:26:24,398
Tell me, Demet, why would she buy

374
00:26:24,399 --> 00:26:30,080
that necklace anyway? More importantly, for whom?

375
00:26:31,240 --> 00:26:34,678
If she had bought it for me, she would have given it to me, I guess.

376
00:26:34,679 --> 00:26:37,199
No, I mean I’m thinking, I’m looking to see if there’s anyone else

377
00:26:37,200 --> 00:26:40,640
he could have bought it for.

378
00:26:40,840 --> 00:26:44,240
There’s Monika

379
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:47,719
for sure. He bought that necklace for her.

380
00:26:47,720 --> 00:26:51,399
What’s that supposed to mean now?

381
00:26:51,520 --> 00:26:55,158
Come on, don’t think the worst right away. Maybe

382
00:26:55,159 --> 00:27:00,080
he bought it for Müzeyyen or Aslı. Isn’t that possible?

383
00:27:10,520 --> 00:27:13,719
Thanks. No need, Cemal.

384
00:27:13,720 --> 00:27:17,398
She’ll just slam the door in my face again.

385
00:27:17,399 --> 00:27:21,440
If I could just understand what she’s trying to do.

386
00:27:22,320 --> 00:27:24,722
She says it can’t be, but then she goes and

387
00:27:24,723 --> 00:27:28,000
has the frame made.
[music]

388
00:27:28,399 --> 00:27:30,239
You know these love affairs are always

389
00:27:30,240 --> 00:27:34,159
complicated anyway, aren’t they, Ateş?
[music]

390
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:37,479
I mean, you know, you chase after her
[music]

391
00:27:37,480 --> 00:27:40,398
she runs away. Then you pull back a bit

392
00:27:40,399 --> 00:27:43,359
and she starts chasing you.

393
00:27:43,360 --> 00:27:44,918
Sometimes you both meet in the middle

394
00:27:44,919 --> 00:27:46,999
and you’re happy. Though to be honest
[music]

395
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:49,038
it’s never happened for me, they usually

396
00:27:49,039 --> 00:27:50,479
run away from me.

397
00:27:50,480 --> 00:27:53,439
Harsh truth. What can you do? But what I mean is,

398
00:27:53,440 --> 00:27:55,959
you can walk through the door and reach

399
00:27:55,960 --> 00:27:58,119
the garden of paradise directly. Or you can

400
00:27:58,120 --> 00:28:02,600
just stand there in front of that door and wait.

401
00:28:10,720 --> 00:28:13,479
He was supposed to be unable to live without me. Supposedly dying

402
00:28:13,480 --> 00:28:16,079
for me.

403
00:28:16,080 --> 00:28:18,319
Out of respect for his love, a person would at least wait

404
00:28:18,320 --> 00:28:21,360
two days.

405
00:28:22,679 --> 00:28:25,479
What kind of dying is that if he pops back to life the moment he sees Monika,

406
00:28:25,480 --> 00:28:29,440
just like that, seriously.

407
00:28:31,600 --> 00:28:33,599
Running off to buy necklaces for another girl

408
00:28:33,600 --> 00:28:35,319
and all that...

409
00:28:35,320 --> 00:28:38,799
turns out he really was untrustworthy.

410
00:28:39,440 --> 00:28:42,518
It burned right here.

411
00:28:42,519 --> 00:28:44,719
If Ateş really bought the necklace for Monika,

412
00:28:44,720 --> 00:28:48,619
that’s wrong. You’re right. [laughter]

413
00:28:50,559 --> 00:28:52,439
But if he bought it for you and is afraid

414
00:28:52,440 --> 00:28:54,959
to give it, that’s because of you, Mercan.

415
00:28:54,960 --> 00:28:58,119
Let me remind you. You turned him down. I

416
00:28:58,120 --> 00:28:59,759
did the right thing.

417
00:28:59,760 --> 00:29:03,080
I’m glad I turned him down.

418
00:29:13,039 --> 00:29:17,558
But I’ve put that girl through so much.

419
00:29:17,559 --> 00:29:21,240
Her attitude is perfectly normal.

420
00:29:21,720 --> 00:29:26,120
What we had was hopeless from the start anyway.

421
00:29:26,399 --> 00:29:29,880
But it’s so hard.

422
00:29:32,600 --> 00:29:36,159
Being this [music] close

423
00:29:37,760 --> 00:29:39,599
and at the same time so far apart is so

424
00:29:39,600 --> 00:29:42,880
hard,

425
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:45,278
it’s like there’s this solid glass wall between us.

426
00:29:45,279 --> 00:29:48,079
I keep trying to break it, to smash it,

427
00:29:48,080 --> 00:29:51,720
but it doesn’t work.

428
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:54,719
I’m the one who put that wall there too.

429
00:29:54,720 --> 00:29:56,740
[music]

430
00:29:58,679 --> 00:30:02,600
How is Cemal supposed to get past this tree?

431
00:30:07,159 --> 00:30:10,559
Is there no way out?

432
00:30:17,640 --> 00:30:20,798
Is there any way out, Demet?

433
00:30:20,799 --> 00:30:24,640
Please tell me there is.

434
00:30:25,640 --> 00:30:28,639
Because living like this is so hard.

435
00:30:28,640 --> 00:30:30,719
I mean, I don’t know why I’m like this either.

436
00:30:30,720 --> 00:30:33,720
Something inside me

437
00:30:36,641 --> 00:30:37,279
[music]

438
00:30:37,280 --> 00:30:40,678
says “come on,” but then it says “stop”

439
00:30:40,679 --> 00:30:43,679
again.

440
00:30:45,919 --> 00:30:49,759
I’m just about to say “okay, I’ll tell you,”

441
00:30:49,760 --> 00:30:54,000
but then I remember what happened.

442
00:30:55,639 --> 00:30:58,599
It’s a 187-day-long marriage. Then what

443
00:30:58,600 --> 00:31:01,600
will happen?

444
00:31:01,679 --> 00:31:03,319
What I’ve lived through is wrapped around my feet

445
00:31:03,320 --> 00:31:05,398
like chains.

446
00:31:05,399 --> 00:31:07,359
I can’t move forward,

447
00:31:07,360 --> 00:31:10,518
and I can’t go back either.

448
00:31:10,519 --> 00:31:14,679
I’m stuck where I am.

449
00:31:16,240 --> 00:31:18,879
I’m so tired of thinking, Demet.

450
00:31:18,880 --> 00:31:22,080
I’m exhausted.

451
00:31:49,880 --> 00:31:52,079
Come on, auntie, [music] why are you giving me such

452
00:31:52,080 --> 00:31:53,959
heavy things? I can handle it.

453
00:31:53,960 --> 00:31:55,239
They’re not even that heavy.

454
00:31:55,240 --> 00:31:56,759
Really, I can handle it. Could you please

455
00:31:56,760 --> 00:31:58,759
give it to me?

456
00:31:58,760 --> 00:32:00,079
Why are you doing things like this?

457
00:32:00,080 --> 00:32:02,879
Please don’t. Today everyone suddenly

458
00:32:02,880 --> 00:32:04,479
decided to do good deeds.

459
00:32:04,480 --> 00:32:05,798
But you only just [music]

460
00:32:05,799 --> 00:32:08,999
got back on your feet, thank God. God forbid

461
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:12,879
something happens. Don’t do this, don’t lift

462
00:32:12,880 --> 00:32:14,439
such heavy things. I’m around here. Call

463
00:32:14,440 --> 00:32:16,158
me for things like this.

464
00:32:16,159 --> 00:32:18,719
Son, I can handle it. You weren’t around.

465
00:32:18,720 --> 00:32:21,439
How can you say that? If we’re not going to

466
00:32:21,440 --> 00:32:23,479
help each other and make each other’s lives

467
00:32:23,480 --> 00:32:25,199
easier, what’s the point of

468
00:32:25,200 --> 00:32:29,159
being together? Isn’t that right?

469
00:32:31,760 --> 00:32:33,999
Okay fine. Here you go. May God [music]

470
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:34,679
bless you,

471
00:32:34,680 --> 00:32:36,558
dear. What do you mean, Auntie? It’s nothing

472
00:32:36,559 --> 00:32:39,638
to even mention, anytime. How are you now?

473
00:32:39,639 --> 00:32:41,239
I’m fine. We just keep rolling [music]

474
00:32:41,240 --> 00:32:44,839
from here to there. I’ll take it.

475
00:32:44,840 --> 00:32:46,199
No, I would’ve handled it.

476
00:32:46,200 --> 00:32:51,120
No, no, no need. I’ll take it, please let go.

477
00:32:53,080 --> 00:32:55,359
Alright then, I’ll go. So

478
00:32:55,360 --> 00:32:57,439
if there’s anything to be carried, please

479
00:32:57,440 --> 00:32:58,999
let me know. I’ll be around.

480
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:02,000
I’m nearby.

481
00:33:05,240 --> 00:33:06,759
Have a nice day.

482
00:33:06,760 --> 00:33:09,879
Take it easy, son.

483
00:33:09,880 --> 00:33:12,038
Girl, you should’ve let him, he could’ve carried it.

484
00:33:12,039 --> 00:33:14,719
No need, mom.

485
00:33:14,720 --> 00:33:17,839
So, what happened? Is the food ready?

486
00:33:17,840 --> 00:33:20,638
It is.

487
00:33:20,639 --> 00:33:22,239
and since you’ve chopped the onions too [music]

488
00:33:22,240 --> 00:33:25,038
I’m sure it’s done.

489
00:33:25,039 --> 00:33:26,759
I know you’re trying to get me to talk

490
00:33:26,760 --> 00:33:29,759
I’m aware, but don’t you worry.

491
00:33:29,760 --> 00:33:33,079
Alright? Turns out I wasn’t as

492
00:33:33,080 --> 00:33:36,278
in love as I thought.

493
00:33:36,279 --> 00:33:37,999
I don’t know how I’m going to convince you,

494
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:42,959
but you just put your mind at ease, okay?

495
00:33:42,960 --> 00:33:45,319
A mother’s heart, you know, my girl,

496
00:33:45,320 --> 00:33:47,879
after this illness, I don’t know,

497
00:33:47,880 --> 00:33:51,638
my head is just

498
00:33:51,639 --> 00:33:53,678
anyway, okay [music] she didn’t ask, she didn’t say

499
00:33:53,679 --> 00:33:54,839
let it be

500
00:33:54,840 --> 00:33:57,479
I know you’re thinking of us.

501
00:33:57,480 --> 00:33:58,798
Alright, alright, I won't open it anymore [music]

502
00:33:58,799 --> 00:34:00,079
the subject

503
00:34:00,080 --> 00:34:03,559
Don't bring it up, mom.

504
00:34:03,880 --> 00:34:05,558
I wonder where Berat is.

505
00:34:05,559 --> 00:34:09,120
Who knows where he is?

506
00:34:11,483 --> 00:34:13,503
[music]

507
00:34:15,280 --> 00:34:16,959
Okay.

508
00:34:16,960 --> 00:34:20,158
Okay. If it happens

509
00:34:20,159 --> 00:34:22,439
friends, friends, everyone listen to me

510
00:34:22,440 --> 00:34:24,039
I’m going to give you very important, very important

511
00:34:24,040 --> 00:34:26,158
news. Really important.

512
00:34:26,159 --> 00:34:30,159
I need to tell you right away.

513
00:34:35,159 --> 00:34:38,158
Mr. Ateş, Mr. Ateş, you come too, please.

514
00:34:38,159 --> 00:34:39,519
What are you doing? Have you lost your mind?

515
00:34:39,520 --> 00:34:41,358
I have, Ms. Zahide. When you hear the news,

516
00:34:41,359 --> 00:34:43,959
you’ll lose it too, because Mr. Ateş also

517
00:34:43,960 --> 00:34:47,720
needs to hear this news.

518
00:34:48,280 --> 00:34:51,879
Mr. Ateş is coming too.

519
00:34:53,079 --> 00:34:56,199
Oh my noble colleagues.

520
00:34:56,200 --> 00:34:59,399
The tireless soldiers of our company.

521
00:34:59,400 --> 00:35:01,239
My friends who never lose focus,

522
00:35:01,240 --> 00:35:03,439
who never let any task slip through their fingers.

523
00:35:03,440 --> 00:35:07,240
Don’t think I don’t notice.

524
00:35:08,560 --> 00:35:11,239
According to the news I just got, our project

525
00:35:11,240 --> 00:35:15,018
has made it to the finals in Italy. Success.

526
00:35:15,019 --> 00:35:17,039
[applause]

527
00:35:20,259 --> 00:35:22,279
[music]

528
00:35:24,189 --> 00:35:26,209
[applause]

529
00:35:44,599 --> 00:35:47,078
Ateş, I really congratulate you [music]

530
00:35:47,079 --> 00:35:50,800
but we didn’t work that hard, guys.

531
00:35:57,594 --> 00:35:59,614
[music]

532
00:35:59,880 --> 00:36:03,240
Mr. Ateş,

533
00:36:06,960 --> 00:36:08,358
I can’t even describe what I feel

534
00:36:08,359 --> 00:36:11,359
you can see it.

535
