Don’t get upset anymore, Ermin. They’ll be out of

1323
01:28:55,320 --> 01:28:58,520
our lives soon.

1324
01:29:04,960 --> 01:29:08,959
As if my only problem was that witch Müzeyyen.

1325
01:29:08,960 --> 01:29:12,320
My real problem is something else.

1326
01:29:13,280 --> 01:29:16,079
It's time to talk to him. Go,

1327
01:29:16,080 --> 01:29:19,440
I'll come right away.

1328
01:29:24,719 --> 01:29:28,238
Nothing will matter anymore, Demet.

1329
01:29:28,239 --> 01:29:30,079
I want to run away to somewhere

1330
01:29:30,080 --> 01:29:32,599
no one can find me.

1331
01:29:32,600 --> 01:29:36,559
Maybe you really should get away.

1332
01:29:36,560 --> 01:29:39,279
I mean at least for a while.

1333
01:29:39,280 --> 01:29:44,198
Germany, for example. Is Pınar still there?

1334
01:29:44,199 --> 01:29:48,039
She was there, as far as I know.

1335
01:29:48,040 --> 01:29:50,999
Why not?

1336
01:29:51,000 --> 01:29:55,040
If you want, I can look for a ticket for you.

1337
01:29:57,080 --> 01:29:59,559
Okay.

1338
01:29:59,560 --> 01:30:03,212
Wait, let me check right now. [music]

1339
01:30:07,119 --> 01:30:08,919
You're very lucky, Mercan. I found

1340
01:30:08,920 --> 01:30:11,920
a ticket for today.

1341
01:30:13,520 --> 01:30:16,319
Don't buy the ticket, don't tell anyone,

1342
01:30:16,320 --> 01:30:20,440
okay? Don't tell anybody.

1343
01:30:21,080 --> 01:30:23,638
I'll leave quietly.

1344
01:30:23,639 --> 01:30:27,880
I'll call later and tell everyone.

1345
01:30:28,159 --> 01:30:31,400
I don't know why

1346
01:30:31,600 --> 01:30:34,039
you're crying.

1347
01:30:34,040 --> 01:30:37,040
I don't know.

1348
01:30:37,840 --> 01:30:40,959
You love him so much, don't you? That's why

1349
01:30:40,960 --> 01:30:43,960
you can't let go.

1350
01:30:45,732 --> 01:30:46,560
[music]

1351
01:30:46,561 --> 01:30:48,479
Then say it, Mercan.

1352
01:30:48,480 --> 01:30:50,678
Don’t think about what comes next.

1353
01:30:50,679 --> 01:30:54,800
You can’t live like this either.

1354
01:30:56,080 --> 01:31:02,080
I can’t.

1355
01:31:04,727 --> 01:31:05,959
[music]

1356
01:31:05,960 --> 01:31:08,238
I’m hanging up now. Come on.

1357
01:31:08,239 --> 01:31:11,600
Okay, honey.

1358
01:31:21,600 --> 01:31:23,678
If you have the dress Ateş bought you for your birthday,

1359
01:31:23,679 --> 01:31:25,678
you should wear that, I think.

1360
01:31:25,679 --> 01:31:30,400
Oh, good thing you reminded me, I have it with me.

1361
01:31:36,719 --> 01:31:41,000
I don’t understand what Ateş sees in this girl.

1362
01:31:41,880 --> 01:31:43,959
It’s not that Ateş sees something in her.

1363
01:31:43,960 --> 01:31:47,238
She’s the one chasing after Ateş.

1364
01:31:47,239 --> 01:31:49,839
She’s chasing after someone like Ateş. Of course

1365
01:31:49,840 --> 01:31:51,919
she would.

1366
01:31:51,920 --> 01:31:53,999
No, what’s with you? Why are you still

1367
01:31:54,000 --> 01:31:56,399
chasing after Ateş? Just

1368
01:31:56,400 --> 01:31:58,959
leave him alone a bit. He doesn’t even

1369
01:31:58,960 --> 01:32:01,118
look at your face.

1370
01:32:01,119 --> 01:32:03,919
What’s it to you, girl? Is it your business

1371
01:32:03,920 --> 01:32:06,839
what I do?

1372
01:32:06,840 --> 01:32:09,519
It’s time for you to go. Tomorrow

1373
01:32:09,520 --> 01:32:11,238
let’s buy your plane ticket. [music]

1374
01:32:11,239 --> 01:32:14,359
And Monika, sweetie, you stay out of this.

1375
01:32:14,360 --> 01:32:16,399
You’re here for Ateş

1376
01:32:16,400 --> 01:32:17,799
You didn’t come. Okay, my girl?

1377
01:32:17,800 --> 01:32:19,678
Okay, I can manage.

1378
01:32:19,679 --> 01:32:23,198
But don’t you dare forget.

1379
01:32:23,199 --> 01:32:25,158
Come on, let’s go take a walk toward that lake

1380
01:32:25,159 --> 01:32:28,840
and look around. Let’s stroll a bit.

1381
01:32:50,839 --> 01:32:52,859
[music]

1382
01:33:09,179 --> 01:33:11,199
[music]

1383
01:33:13,880 --> 01:33:17,960
Pull, let me help you.

1384
01:33:19,004 --> 01:33:21,024
[music]

1385
01:33:24,960 --> 01:33:28,760
Then I’m leaving it like this.

1386
01:33:29,520 --> 01:33:31,718
So I’ve left it like this then.

1387
01:33:31,719 --> 01:33:34,479
Thank you

1388
01:33:34,480 --> 01:33:36,399
so much. How’s the soup? It’s really good.

1389
01:33:36,400 --> 01:33:37,320
Bless your hands.

1390
01:33:37,321 --> 01:33:41,000
Enjoy it, my son.

1391
01:33:41,920 --> 01:33:47,560
Well then, good luck with your work, Malik.

1392
01:33:47,639 --> 01:33:49,879
So, son, finish up your work and

1393
01:33:49,880 --> 01:33:51,118
come over to the annex in Milata [music]. We’ll

1394
01:33:51,119 --> 01:33:55,079
have a cup of tea together.

1395
01:33:55,080 --> 01:33:58,599
Won’t I tire you out? I mean, you’ve only just

1396
01:33:58,600 --> 01:34:00,519
got back on your feet.

1397
01:34:00,520 --> 01:34:02,839
No, son, I won’t get tired. You just come,

1398
01:34:02,840 --> 01:34:05,799
we’ll have our tea.

1399
01:34:05,800 --> 01:34:07,919
Alright. Since you say so, I’ll come. So,

1400
01:34:07,920 --> 01:34:09,839
should I bring something when I come, would you like…

1401
01:34:09,840 --> 01:34:11,279
Would you? I mean, do you want me to do something

1402
01:34:11,280 --> 01:34:15,238
for you? No need, son. Just come, that’s enough.

1403
01:34:15,239 --> 01:34:18,239
Okay.

1404
01:34:19,320 --> 01:34:20,479
See you.

1405
01:34:20,480 --> 01:34:21,559
Take care, good luck with your work.

1406
01:34:21,560 --> 01:34:24,718
Thanks.

1407
01:34:24,719 --> 01:34:27,919
Mom, are you okay?

1408
01:34:27,920 --> 01:34:29,198
I’m fine, my girl.

1409
01:34:29,199 --> 01:34:31,319
Why did you call the accountant?

1410
01:34:31,320 --> 01:34:33,039
I’ve got business with him.

1411
01:34:33,040 --> 01:34:35,678
What business?

1412
01:34:35,679 --> 01:34:37,238
At this age, do I have to answer

1413
01:34:37,239 --> 01:34:38,959
to my daughter? What business would I have? [music]

1414
01:34:38,960 --> 01:34:40,479
I just have business, that’s all. Why do you

1415
01:34:40,480 --> 01:34:43,359
care? Oh, come on. I was just curious,

1416
01:34:43,360 --> 01:34:45,359
that’s all. How should I know?

1417
01:34:45,360 --> 01:34:47,359
Don’t be curious, my girl, don’t. [music]

1418
01:34:47,360 --> 01:34:50,840
You’ll find out when the time comes anyway.

1419
01:34:51,360 --> 01:34:53,380
[music]

1420
01:34:58,565 --> 01:35:00,585
[music]

1421
01:35:18,760 --> 01:35:21,760
Şırdır

1422
01:35:28,041 --> 01:35:30,061
[music]

1423
01:35:37,080 --> 01:35:38,759
Where are you traveling to?

1424
01:35:38,760 --> 01:35:40,359
Uh,

1425
01:35:40,360 --> 01:35:42,450
what trip, dear? Where’d you get that from?

1426
01:35:42,451 --> 01:35:43,799
[music]

1427
01:35:43,800 --> 01:35:45,718
I was just tidying up my clothes,

1428
01:35:45,719 --> 01:35:47,359
having a look.

1429
01:35:47,360 --> 01:35:50,879
I mean, do women do that sometimes?

1430
01:35:50,880 --> 01:35:54,880
Apparently women do it sometimes.

1431
01:35:54,920 --> 01:35:56,439
I see.

1432
01:35:56,440 --> 01:35:58,718
Where were you? You disappeared

1433
01:35:58,719 --> 01:36:01,718
without saying anything.

1434
01:36:01,719 --> 01:36:04,919
Do I have to let you know?

1435
01:36:04,920 --> 01:36:06,519
Do you inform me about everywhere

1436
01:36:06,520 --> 01:36:08,638
you go?

1437
01:36:08,639 --> 01:36:12,198
I mean, I went out early and walked around a bit. Were you

1438
01:36:12,199 --> 01:36:14,718
that worried?

1439
01:36:14,719 --> 01:36:17,238
No, I wasn’t.

1440
01:36:17,239 --> 01:36:18,439
You don’t want me to worry [music]

1441
01:36:18,440 --> 01:36:20,198
about you anyway.

1442
01:36:20,199 --> 01:36:23,480
Yeah, I don’t.

1443
01:36:23,600 --> 01:36:26,599
Don’t worry about me. Worry about your kit friends,

1444
01:36:26,600 --> 01:36:29,238
for example

1445
01:36:29,239 --> 01:36:31,158
pay attention to Monika or something. Maybe you’ll

1446
01:36:31,159 --> 01:36:33,540
take her out to dinner. Why did I drag

1447
01:36:33,541 --> 01:36:34,080
[music]

1448
01:36:34,081 --> 01:36:37,360
Monika into this now?

1449
01:36:44,199 --> 01:36:48,000
What does Monika have to do with this?

1450
01:36:49,760 --> 01:36:53,799
Aren’t you late for the company, anyway?

1451
01:36:53,800 --> 01:36:57,119
I'm not going today.

1452
01:36:58,480 --> 01:37:01,039
Why aren't you going? There's tons of work to do

1453
01:37:01,040 --> 01:37:03,999
I mean. I think you should go and be at your job.

1454
01:37:04,000 --> 01:37:06,291
I'm going to work from home today. That's what I'll do

1455
01:37:06,292 --> 01:37:08,678
anyway, with the music. Don't worry.

1456
01:37:08,679 --> 01:37:11,039
It can't work if you keep working from home like that.

1457
01:37:11,040 --> 01:37:13,479
You need to go and be there. And

1458
01:37:13,480 --> 01:37:15,599
didn't you have a meeting today?

1459
01:37:15,600 --> 01:37:19,391
No, I canceled them all.

1460
01:37:19,392 --> 01:37:21,412
[music]

1461
01:37:29,760 --> 01:37:33,801
Why are you so hung up on me not going?

1462
01:37:33,802 --> 01:37:33,920
[music]

1463
01:37:33,921 --> 01:37:36,118
Why would I be hung up?

1464
01:37:36,119 --> 01:37:38,238
I just said it because there's work. Otherwise it's

1465
01:37:38,239 --> 01:37:39,598
none of my business. Where you go, what

1466
01:37:39,599 --> 01:37:40,959
you do.

1467
01:37:40,960 --> 01:37:43,238
I mean it's none of my business.

1468
01:37:43,239 --> 01:37:45,359
Yeah. Right.

1469
01:37:45,360 --> 01:37:49,239
Why don't you go to the company?

1470
01:37:49,280 --> 01:37:51,839
I've taken care of my work.

1471
01:37:51,840 --> 01:37:53,519
I won't be going for a while either.

1472
01:37:53,520 --> 01:37:56,198
Oh really? Why?

1473
01:37:56,199 --> 01:37:58,198
Because I feel like it.

1474
01:37:58,199 --> 01:38:01,840
You should have finished your work first.

1475
01:38:02,760 --> 01:38:06,678
Demet and I finished ours. While you were at lunch.

1476
01:38:06,679 --> 01:38:09,118
Hmm,

1477
01:38:09,119 --> 01:38:12,119
I understand.

1478
01:38:13,599 --> 01:38:17,559
Dinner was really delicious yesterday, too.

1479
01:38:17,560 --> 01:38:21,198
May God make it sit well in your hearts.

1480
01:38:21,199 --> 01:38:25,159
I'll be in the study.

1481
01:38:25,960 --> 01:38:27,799
I don't want to be disturbed. [music]

1482
01:38:27,800 --> 01:38:28,679
Accordingly

1483
01:38:28,680 --> 01:38:31,679
we won't.

1484
01:38:32,098 --> 01:38:34,118
[music]

1485
01:38:37,599 --> 01:38:40,678
Listen to what he's saying.

1486
01:38:40,679 --> 01:38:41,919
No, no.

1487
01:38:41,920 --> 01:38:44,638
I made the right decision.

1488
01:38:44,639 --> 01:38:47,880
Let me go so he can be rid of me.

1489
01:38:56,988 --> 01:38:59,008
[music]

1490
01:39:28,679 --> 01:39:30,079
Berat [laughter]

1491
01:39:30,080 --> 01:39:33,080
Zehra

1492
01:39:34,040 --> 01:39:37,679
what happened? What happened?

1493
01:39:37,840 --> 01:39:38,719
What happened?

1494
01:39:38,720 --> 01:39:40,919
The flower

1495
01:39:40,920 --> 01:39:42,198
what happened? I feel like the flower

1496
01:39:42,199 --> 01:39:44,399
is going to separate us.

1497
01:39:44,400 --> 01:39:48,079
It even came into my dreams last night.

1498
01:39:48,080 --> 01:39:49,718
My dear child, why do you dwell

1499
01:39:49,719 --> 01:39:51,039
on things like this? I thought something

1500
01:39:51,040 --> 01:39:53,479
had happened. Ah

1501
01:39:53,480 --> 01:39:55,319
So you even saw me in your dream, huh? The flower

1502
01:39:55,320 --> 01:39:58,399
what are you going to do if you see her? Besides, that's a nightmare.

1503
01:39:58,400 --> 01:39:59,678
It's not a dream.

1504
01:39:59,679 --> 01:40:02,759
Don't say that. It affects a person,

1505
01:40:02,760 --> 01:40:05,718
you know, my beauty.

1506
01:40:05,719 --> 01:40:07,799
No matter what she does, she can't

1507
01:40:07,800 --> 01:40:10,279
get to me. Don't worry. Look, we’re

1508
01:40:10,280 --> 01:40:12,718
so good together.

1509
01:40:12,719 --> 01:40:15,359
You’re way too relaxed, Berat. I’m telling you she’s there.

1510
01:40:15,360 --> 01:40:19,399
She keeps warning me all the time.

1511
01:40:19,400 --> 01:40:20,839
What does she

1512
01:40:20,840 --> 01:40:23,319
say? She says leave my brother alone, break up with him,

1513
01:40:23,320 --> 01:40:26,519
stuff like that.

1514
01:40:26,520 --> 01:40:29,319
Wow, what a messed‑up mind.

1515
01:40:29,320 --> 01:40:32,598
Just don’t look, don’t pay attention.

1516
01:40:32,599 --> 01:40:36,480
I can’t ignore it. Berat

1517
01:40:36,639 --> 01:40:38,919
is going to break us up, I know it.

1518
01:40:38,920 --> 01:40:42,519
And she’s your sister, your family.

1519
01:40:42,520 --> 01:40:45,279
Of course it’s normal for you to listen to them.

1520
01:40:45,280 --> 01:40:47,678
What’s that supposed to mean? You should say, “You’re also the girl

1521
01:40:47,679 --> 01:40:50,479
I love.” Right,

1522
01:40:50,480 --> 01:40:53,959
my beautiful? Don’t pay attention to “the flower.” She acts like that

1523
01:40:53,960 --> 01:40:56,198
at first, that’s normal, but

1524
01:40:56,199 --> 01:40:58,799
she doesn’t have a bad heart. Don’t worry.

1525
01:40:58,800 --> 01:41:02,198
She does, Berat, she will.

1526
01:41:02,199 --> 01:41:03,959
Now that you objected to him owning the mansion

1527
01:41:03,960 --> 01:41:06,519
he’s taking all his anger out on me.

1528
01:41:06,520 --> 01:41:08,079
He’s venting it all on me.

1529
01:41:08,080 --> 01:41:09,999
He keeps making snide little remarks

1530
01:41:10,000 --> 01:41:11,959
at every opportunity.

1531
01:41:11,960 --> 01:41:13,879
I can’t take it anymore, Berat.

1532
01:41:13,880 --> 01:41:16,759
My beautiful one, my rose. Look

1533
01:41:16,760 --> 01:41:19,718
at me. Come on. No one can separate us. I

1534
01:41:19,719 --> 01:41:22,519
won’t be influenced. Don’t worry.

1535
01:41:22,520 --> 01:41:26,880
Okay, wipe those tears now.

1536
01:41:27,040 --> 01:41:30,960
I think the only solution is that we get married.

1537
01:41:33,920 --> 01:41:35,439
What do you mean, get married?

1538
01:41:35,440 --> 01:41:37,799
Get married, that’s what.

1539
01:41:37,800 --> 01:41:43,000
I get it. But marriage

1540
01:41:43,280 --> 01:41:45,359
I mean, where did that come from now?

1541
01:41:45,360 --> 01:41:47,799
Aren’t we together anyway?

1542
01:41:47,800 --> 01:41:50,198
We are, but

1543
01:41:50,199 --> 01:41:51,999
isn’t it too early?

1544
01:41:52,000 --> 01:41:55,158
We talked about this, remember. Berat [laughter]

1545
01:41:55,159 --> 01:41:57,439
we have no other choice. That’s why I’m saying it.

1546
01:41:57,440 --> 01:41:58,718
Of course we talked.

1547
01:41:58,719 --> 01:42:02,520
And we love each other.

1548
01:42:02,840 --> 01:42:04,519
Yeah, we do.

1549
01:42:04,520 --> 01:42:07,238
We do love each other.

1550
01:42:07,239 --> 01:42:10,560
Well then

1551
01:42:10,679 --> 01:42:12,559
I mean

1552
01:42:12,560 --> 01:42:15,560
Berat

1553
01:42:19,320 --> 01:42:21,238
only then no one can come between

1554
01:42:21,239 --> 01:42:24,239
us.

1555
01:42:25,440 --> 01:42:26,959
So they laughed.

1556
01:42:26,960 --> 01:42:31,080
We have no other choice, Berat.

1557
01:42:31,119 --> 01:42:33,718
Otherwise I can't stay

1558
01:42:33,719 --> 01:42:36,719
in this house any longer.

1559
01:42:37,725 --> 01:42:39,745
[music]

1560
01:42:45,586 --> 01:42:47,606
[music]

1561
01:43:11,131 --> 01:43:13,151
[music]

1562
01:43:19,800 --> 01:43:23,239
Hello, Nero.

1563
01:43:23,320 --> 01:43:27,280
Drop the polite act.

1564
01:43:28,639 --> 01:43:30,359
Sir, you can fool others

1565
01:43:30,360 --> 01:43:33,519
with your manners. Not me.

1566
01:43:33,520 --> 01:43:36,519
Why did you want to meet [music]?

1567
01:43:36,520 --> 01:43:39,520
Sit down.

1568
01:43:46,719 --> 01:43:50,880
I know you're Haydar's son.

1569
01:43:55,159 --> 01:43:58,840
Haydar's and Nurgül's.

1570
01:43:58,880 --> 01:44:02,159
Yes, that's right.

1571
01:44:03,520 --> 01:44:05,279
Does Haydar know?

1572
01:44:05,280 --> 01:44:08,920
No. Certainly not.

1573
01:44:09,400 --> 01:44:12,599
What do you want?

1574
01:44:14,667 --> 01:44:16,687
[music]

1575
01:44:17,119 --> 01:44:20,079
You secretly infiltrated the company.

1576
01:44:20,080 --> 01:44:23,279
You even came all the way to the mansion.

1577
01:44:23,280 --> 01:44:26,880
What is your aim?

1578
01:44:29,880 --> 01:44:31,799
Are you looking for trouble?

1579
01:44:31,800 --> 01:44:35,360
I don't want anything.

1580
01:44:35,920 --> 01:44:40,119
I just want to know my father.

1581
01:44:41,400 --> 01:44:44,479
I want to know who I am.

1582
01:44:44,480 --> 01:44:49,119
My only family in this life was my mother.

1583
01:44:50,360 --> 01:44:53,679
I lost her too.

1584
01:44:53,920 --> 01:44:57,079
